deck: Created in pulp books before Batman, Tony Quinn was a brash Defense Attorney to the mob. When he refused to cross the line and was tortured and blinded, Quinn transformed into the Black Bat and embarks on a quest to right the wrongs of his past.
description:
Origin

Tony Quinn was a militant district attorney until a criminal threw acid in his face leaving him blinded and scarred. Swearing that this would not halt his search for justice, he began to train his other senses and body. Later, radical experimental surgery led to him receiving the transplanted eyes of a slain police officer. His new eyes allowed him not only to see, but for some reason, he now found he could also see in the dark. Pretending to still be blind, Tony called himself The Black Bat and kicked his fight against crime into higher gear.

Creation

In the pulp stories, his last name was Quinn and he called himself The Black Bat, who was known for carrying twin .45s and leaving a bat-shaped mark on the foreheads of his victims, as well as driving a modified car to and from his cases.

When Nedor later decided to transfer some of their pulp characters to comics, the Black Bat was one of the first they picked, although they changed his last name to Colby at this time. While they had created the character first, they worked out a deal with DC and changed his name to The Mask. Gone since 1941 from both pulps and comics, Moonstone Comics brought the character back in 2010 under his original name of Tony Quinn as The Black Bat.

Major Story Arcs

Return of the Originals

In February 1945, an mysterious object appeared in the night sky above Los Angeles. Anti-aircraft artillery fired over 1,400 at the object but nothing was brought down. The Phantom Detective, The Black Bat, Domino Lady, G-8, and Secret Agent X team-up battle a strange new menace.

Masks

Black Bat is a member of Dynamite Entertainment's vigilante team Masks. Set in 1938 when The Justice Party has been elected power of New York State, it soon conspires the newly-elected officials are controlled by powerful criminals, who quickly corrupt the law to their own advantage. A fascist police state is instituted and ordinary citizens are brutalised, oppressed and crushed into submission. The only ones who stand up to protect the innocent are masked vigilantes like The Shadow, The Green Hornet, The Spider and The Black Bat.

Powers & Abilities

Black Bat was an adept hand-to-hand combatant and detective, but his main powers are enhanced vision - he can see perfectly in pitch-black darkness. He also carried around twin .45s.

Other Media

Film

Rise of the Black Bat is a movie in 2013 base on the pulp character.

deck: A character from Black Hole.
description:
Origin

Eliza appears in the Kitchen Sink/Fantagraphics title, Black Hole.

Creation

Eliza was created by Charles Burns.

Character Evolution

Eliza is an artist who has a small, reptilian tail - earning her the nickname "Lizard Queen". She is a friend of Keith Pearson. After running away from home because of issues with her step-dad, Eliza ends up living with a group of amateur drug dealers. She keeps the place clean and works on her art in their basement, until a party turns ugly one night, and Eliza is drugged and raped. The gang ten write obscenities and insults all over her body while she is passed out. The second time she meets Keith, he finds that she has changed because of this - she is more subdued, and has destroyed all of her art as she can no longer bear to look at it. In truth, a lot of her art is defaced by the group of young men who attack her. She is the first woman Keith ever sleeps with, and shortly after this, Eliza approaches Keith at work, and gives him her number, asking him to keep in touch. The two eventually fall in love and go on the road together. They decide to take off after a mutated teen named Dave attacks and kills Keith's friends, and then himself.

The tip of Eliza's tail often snaps off. Keith is startled when this happens during intercourse, but she reassures him that feels no pain in her tail, and it regenerates.

Major Story Arcs

Eliza does not appear in any major story arcs.

Powers and Abilities

Eliza has no special powers or abilities.

deck:
Jimmy Corrigan is a depressed and anti-social man, who lives in an apartment, alone. 
The Graphic novel he appears in is considered one of the greatest in the medium.
description:
Origin

Jimmy Corrigan was born to Mrs. Corrigan. Jimmy Corrigan had no relationship with his father when he was growing up, considering his mother kept Jimmy's father's identity a secret for most of his life.

Creation

Jimmy Corrigan was created by Chris Ware. He has written many highly acclaimed graphic novels, including Acme Novelty Library.

Major Story Arcs

Jimmy Corrigan has only appeared in one graphic work: Jimmy Corrigan, the Smartest Kid on Earth. This novel chronicles Jimmy Corrigan's first meeting with his father. Before that meeting, Jimmy had never had any contact with his father. This story reveals how unhappy Jimmy is. Jimmy uses his imagination to escape his unhappiness. The story displays Jimmy's journey to eventual adulthood, by making him rely less on his imagination, and rely more on social interaction. This transition is displayed when Jimmy meets his father's other daughter, for the first time. Their conversations show how much Jimmy struggles during social interactions. At the end of Jimmy's main story arc, he has grown tremendously as a person.

deck: The genre literal for romance. She was called upon by Kevin Thorn for inspiration and then used to protect him from Snow, Bigby, the Page Sisters, and Mr. Revise. Though she doesn't seem she could do much, as she appears to be nothing more than pretty face.
description:
Romance is a beautiful red-headed lady, whom Kevin Thorn quotes "still a slut". She was called upon by Kevin Thorn who was under the influence of Writer's Block. However, he still found even with the genres here, that they were boring. Romance took great offense and acted, though over dramatically, at Kevin. Despite how Kevin tried to calm her, she still took offense.

Elsewhere, Bigby, Snow, Gary, and Mr. Revise; along with the Page Sisters, had come to stop him from doing further damage to reality. Kevin sent the Genres, including Romance to guard his house and fight off the others. Though what damage she could really do is not known, since Romance didn't seem to do anything.

Bigby, who had been put through much humiliation and transformed into a girl to further it, lost his patience. While Robin, Priscilla, and Hillary fought off the others, he snuck around trees and killed all the Genres. Though they appareared dead, after defeating Kevin, Romance and the rest of the Genres had apparently recovered. They were all sent into a new world where Kevin, alongside Mr. Revise, could do what he want and leave the mundy world alone.

She was called upon by Kevin; who was under the influence of Writer's Block. However, he still found even with the genres here, that they were boring. Bigby, Snow, Gary, and Mister Revise; along with the Page Sisters, had come to stop him from doing further damage to reality. Kevin sent the Genres, including Horror to guard his house and fight off the others.

Horror was most likely enjoying all the fighting, but she took great interest, as did Literature, in the battle when they heard Mr. Revise was near. She held a grudge against him for editing the Odyssey and hoped to kill him for it. Bigby, who had been put through much humiliation and transformed into a girl to further it, lost his patience. While Robin, Priscilla, and Hillary fought off the others, he snuck around trees and attacked all the Genres. Horror was the first to see her(Bigby who was still stuck in his little girl form) and immediately ordered the others to kill her(Bigby). Quoting the sweeter they are, the more danger they are; since she spoke from personal experience, given her appearance.

However, Blockbuster and Western refused, as it was a rule not to kill a little girl, especially a child. That would be a mistake as Bigby would show no mercy and kill Horror and the rest of the Genres. For the moment, after defeating Kevin, Horror and the rest of the Genres had apparently recovered. Or it meant they were resurrected by Kevin or simply replaced. They were all sent into a new world where Kevin could do what he want and leave the mundy world alone.

deck: Persian god of evil.
description:
The name is not on the old Persian inscriptions. In the Avesta is called the twin brother of Ahura Mazda, and Spenta Mainyu opposite. is like Satan, considered as the destroyer, the source of all evil in the world and, like Ahura Mazda, existed from creation. Ahriman chose evil consciously, created disease to hasten death. It is considered the biggest evil was corrupt the pure fire was created by Ahura Mazda, which gave added color and smoke, giving it its characteristic pollutant. On the Day of Judgment will be destroyed by Spenta Mainyu and disappear from the world forever.

One can see an analogy with Christian beliefs through the concept of Satan, but not the same as Angra Mainyu is not a being or an entity, Angra Mainyu refers to poor human mentality, misinterpreted as the main agent of evil, Angra Mainyu however not equivalent to Judeo-Christian Satan, differing from this in that, if there is a permanent Zoroastrianism battle between two principles (good and bad), the people of Israel, and later in Christianity, there is a single principle, the creator of everything, including Satan, who rejects this principle good use of their freedom with which it was created. Therefore, in the Judeo-Christian tradition, the reality is positive. But for Zoroastrianism, by balancing opposites is Angra Mainyu against Spenta Mainyu, Zarathustra distinguished the two poles of a particular dynamic: the creation and destruction, referred to as an all in Ahura Mazda.

Samon-kun wa Summoner

In this comedic manga, Angra Mainyu is still portrayed as an ultra baddy and the essence of evil, but she is also in love with the titular character who was the first person to call her friend (being so lonely due to everyone fearing her evil) and thus, her status is mostly diminished over petty fighting for Samon's affection.
